# unso-os Core Guidance

- Read `docs/ai-implementation-brief.md` and follow its decision order when requirements conflict.
- Read `docs/phase-1-auth-onboarding-spec.md` before touching login, onboarding, company setup, or employee request flows.
- Treat Google login and business access as separate states.
- Keep permission control aligned across UI, API, and RLS.
- Do not guess auth, role, company bootstrap, or tenant isolation behavior.
- Keep transport-specific wording configurable so future industries can reuse the product.
- Prefer implementation order: onboarding, roles, master responsibility, then business features.
- Never commit `.env.local` or edit applied migrations in place.
